## Test 2: Tool Access and Real Data

Command: openclaw agent --agent pricelabs --message "Show me my listings"

Response:
---
I can't fetch them right now -- the PriceLabs MCP connection is down
(`MCP server exited`), so I don't have live listing access at the moment.
---

Result: FAIL -- MCP server exited

## Root Cause Analysis

Gateway logs show:
  [plugins] [pricelabs] Spawning MCP server: /mnt/c/Projects/pricelabs-agent/mcp-servers/pricelabs/dist/index.js
  [plugins] [pricelabs] MCP server exited with code

Direct test:
  node /mnt/c/Projects/pricelabs-agent/mcp-servers/pricelabs/dist/index.js
  -> FATAL: PRICELABS_API_KEY environment variable is required

Issue: PRICELABS_API_KEY is not in the gateway's systemd service environment.
The plugin config (plugins.entries.pricelabs) has no config.apiKey set.
The per-agent mcp block (which was supposed to pass env vars) was rejected in Plan 12-01.

## Fix Required

Add PRICELABS_API_KEY to the gateway systemd service:
  sudo systemctl edit openclaw-gateway.service
  -> [Service]
  -> Environment=PRICELABS_API_KEY=<key>

Then: sudo systemctl daemon-reload && sudo systemctl restart openclaw-gateway.service

## Auth Gate

The API key value must be provided by the user. It is not available in:
- Shell environment (empty/unset)
- /home/NGA/.openclaw/.env (only NGA_WORKSPACE)
- /home/NGA/.openclaw/.env.secrets (no PRICELABS entry)
- 1Password (not authenticated)
- openclaw.json plugin config (not set)
- Gateway systemd unit (not set)
